        <strong><h2><ins>Must Do Activities</ins></h2></strong>
        <hr>
          <!-- Writing a paragragh on Taj mahal -->
        <br><strong>1. TAJ MAHAL :</strong><br>The Taj Mahal is a white marble mausoleum in Agra, India, built by Mughal Emperor Shah Jahan for his beloved wife, Mumtaz Mahal, who died during childbirth, making it a renowned symbol of eternal love. Constructed between 1631 and 1653 by over <strong>20,000 artisans,</strong>  it is a masterpiece of Mughal architecture, blending Persian, Islamic, and Indian styles. The complex, located on the banks of the Yamuna River, features formal gardens, a mosque, and a guesthouse, and is recognized as both one of the Seven Wonders of the World and a <em>UNESCO World Heritage Site.</em>  
        <!-- image link via Copy Image Address -->
        <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/d/da/Taj-Mahal.jpg" alt="Taj Mahal stands majestically with its white marble reflecting sunlight, surrounded by lush gardens and visitors admiring the monument. The atmosphere feels serene and awe-inspiring." width="25" height="25"

    <hr>
    <!-- we use images to attract our customer -->
        <!-- Writing a paragraph on River rafting in Rishikesh -->
         <!-- strong use for bold character -->









        <br><strong>2. RIVER RAFTING :</strong><br>River rafting in Rishikesh, India, is an exhilarating adventure activity that involves navigating the white-water rapids of the Ganges River. <strong>Known as the "Yoga Capital of the World,"</strong> Rishikesh offers a unique blend of spiritual serenity and thrilling outdoor experiences. The river's varying levels of rapids cater to both beginners and experienced rafters, making it a popular destination for adventure enthusiasts. Rafting trips often include stunning views of the surrounding Himalayan foothills, lush forests, and ancient temples along the riverbanks. <ins>Safety is a priority,</ins> with professional guides and quality equipment provided to ensure an enjoyable and secure experience. Overall, river rafting in Rishikesh combines excitement with natural beauty, making it a must-do activity for visitors seeking adventure in India.
        <!-- image link via Copy Image Address -->
        <img src="https://www.redchilliadventure.com/system/images/000/054/983/b763ccfc75612b3e4f2e684588f64cee/banner/rafting-4.jpg" alt="Group of people rafting on the Ganga River in Rishikesh, navigating white water rapids with lush green hills in the background. The mood is adventurous and energetic." width="25" height="50"
